WhatsApp claims end-to-end encryption, but backups often aren’t protected by your password, allowing access if backups are stolen or hacked. Similarly, iPhone backups can restore messages without needing encryption keys. This means your chats may be exposed outside the app. True security needs encryption that protects messages even in backups. Research terms like “WhatsApp backup encryption,” “iPhone iCloud backup security,” and “end-to-end encryption limits” to learn more.